SIMPLE: rusty
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rusty
<hw>Rust"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>rustig</ets>.]</ety> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Rustier</adjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Rustiest.</adjf>]</amorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Covered or affected
with rust; <as>as, a <ex>rusty</ex> knife or sword; <ex>rusty</ex>
wheat</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Impaired by inaction, disuse, or neglect.</def> <--
less skillful than when in continued practise -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Hector,] in this dull and long-continued truce,⟦br⟧
Is <qex>rusty</qex> grown.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Discolored and rancid; reasty; <as>as,
<ex>rusty</ex> bacon</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Surly; morose; crusty; sullen.</def> <mark>[Obs. or
Prov. Eng.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Rusty</xex> words.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Piers
Plowman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Rust-colored; dark.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Rusty</xex>
blood.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>Discolored; stained; not cleanly kept;
filthy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>rusty</qex> little schooners that bring firewood from the
British provinces.</q> <rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Resembling, or covered with a
substance resembling, rust; affected with rust; rubiginous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rut</ent>⟦br⟧
